Is mass innovation in the education sector slow because of scalability problems
text: For a very long time people have been repeating the same line: "the education system is outdated and was built on an old Prussian industrial model and change is needed". saying things like school kills creativity etc. Despite this very little has changed for the majority of people (mainly those in the public education system); and there are a handful of school systems/schools that have solved this problem all over the US but it seems to just stop there. I know trying to innovate in the public education sector is slow for obvious reasons but shouldn't the private sector be able to scale easier, or at least at a faster pace than it is now.

Ask HN: OpenAI, easy in, no way out?
text:
It took all of 2 minutes to create an OpenAI account to try out chat.openai.com. Now I'd like to delete (create > delete) my account. I've found a mix of approaches and tried them all.

So far, my requests have gone unanswered.

title: Ask HN: My email address is being used by someone else for Banking
text:
It has been going on for quite some time ( years ) . At first I thought the email was a scam so I ignored it. And later I realise it is from a Real US Bank. I continue to ignore it thinking the owner surely one day will change it.

I have 2FA and I am pretty sure my email account is safe and not compromised.

Now I am thinking should I do something about this? If yes then what? Or should I continue to ignore it?

It has also been a long time since I opened a bank account. But shouldn't bank verify the email address?
